	<section>
		<gotoAndPlay label="start" />
		<text><b>Rests</b> are used to show periods of silence in a bar.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="notes" />
		<text>Each type of rest shares a duration with a certain type of note.</text>
		<gotoAndStop label="notes2" />
		<text>For example, both a crotchet rest and a crotchet note occupy the same amount of time.  While the note would make a sound, the rest is silent.</text>
	</section>
			
	<section>
		<gotoAndPlay label="example" />
		<text>To demonstrate this, we will fill a bar of 4/4 time with crotchet notes.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="example2" />
		<text>Listen to the above example.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="example3" />
		<text>Next, we will replace the second crotchet note with a crotchet rest.</text>
		<gotoAndPlay label="example4" />
		<text>Notice how the second beat is now silent.</text>
	</section>	

